<br>
Does root ever become relatively reliable? I'm 22 now, trying to practice the root an' DoT technique, and it feels like if I cast any spell at all on the target root breaks. It's so unstable I feel like I could give that stupid sensate reishi elder a HP buff and it'd break root. <br>
<br>
Any advice fer a young shaman too dumb ta run when root breaks? <br>
<br>
-Winteris <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krogothbitterstar>KrogothBitterstar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/14/03 6:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=144.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stupid root spell...</span><hr size=1> Root or any DD has a chance to break root. It hasn't got really reliable for me.<br>
<br>
At your level I would just tank to be honest....I tanked all the way up to my high 40s.<br>
<br>
Drop a slow on the mob, stick a DoT on it and use a few nukes.<br>
<br>
Now I don't use nukes really at all at my level (51) because it's not that efficient....but at your level I did.<br>
<br>
Once you get 34 all this will become a little bit easier with your pet - you can just run round in circles : )<br>
<br>
Also, tanking will help you get your defense skill capped. I didn't get mine fully capped 'till I was in my 40s and I'm glad I did. I now have 1000ac and feel it has saved me a fair few times : )<br>
<br>
I have yet to come anywhere near capping my wis and 190 is enough for me as it is : ) Most important stats to me now are AC/HP/wis/mana in that order.<br>
<br>
